Notar que hay valores 0 y 1, que se consideran double, cuando claramente puede ser booleanos, al igual que la variable Sex puede ser tomada como boolean, solo identificar bien como se etiquetan las variables para la interpretaci√≥n.

data_raw$`Differential Count` <- factor(data_raw$`Differential Count`, 
                                        levels = c(0, 1), 
                                        labels = c("No", "Yes"))

data_raw$`RBC PANEL` <- factor(data_raw$`RBC PANEL`, 
                               levels = c(0, 1), 
                               labels = c("No", "Yes"))

data_raw$`Final Output` <- factor(data_raw$`Final Output`, 
                                  levels = c(0, 1), 
                                  labels = c("Negative", "Positive"))
View(data_raw)

# Gr√°fico de dispersi√≥n entre variables continuas

     main = "Edad vs Haemoglobina",
     xlab = "Edad", ylab = "Haemoglobina",
     col = "steelblue", pch = 16)

     main = "WBC Count vs Platelet Count",

# Boxplot de Haemoglobina seg√∫n sexo
boxplot(Haemoglobin ~ Sex, data = data_raw,
        main = "Haemoglobina seg√∫n Sexo",
        col = c("skyblue", "salmon"),
        ylab = "Haemoglobina")

# Boxplot de WBC Count seg√∫n resultado final
boxplot(`WBC Count` ~ `Final Output`, data = data_raw,
        main = "WBC Count seg√∫n Final Output",
        col = c("lightgreen", "gold"),
        ylab = "WBC Count")

# Boxplot de PDW seg√∫n Differential Count
boxplot(PDW ~ `Differential Count`, data = data_raw,
        main = "PDW seg√∫n Differential Count",
        col = c("pink", "lightblue"),
        ylab = "PDW")

# Tabla de contingencia
tabla_dc_final <- table(data_raw$`Differential Count`, data_raw$`Final Output`)
print(tabla_dc_final)
##      
##       Negative Positive
##   No         0       60
##   Yes      320      609
# Barras agrupadas
barplot(tabla_dc_final,
        beside = TRUE,
        col = c("lightblue", "lightpink"),
        legend = TRUE,
        main = "Final Output seg√∫n Differential Count",
        ylab = "Frecuencia")

# Otra tabla: Sex vs Final Output
tabla_sex_final <- table(data_raw$Sex, data_raw$`Final Output`)
barplot(tabla_sex_final,
        beside = TRUE,
        col = c("lightcyan", "lightcoral"),
        legend = TRUE,
        main = "Final Output seg√∫n Sexo")

library(corrplot)
## corrplot 0.95 loaded
numeric_vars <- data_raw[, c("Age", "Haemoglobin", "WBC Count", "Platelet Count", "PDW")]

# Matriz de correlaci√≥n
cor_matrix <- cor(numeric_vars, use = "complete.obs")

# Gr√°fico
corrplot(cor_matrix, method = "color", type = "upper", 
         tl.col = "black", tl.srt = 45,
         addCoef.col = "black", # muestra los coeficientes
         col = colorRampPalette(c("red", "white", "blue"))(200))
